Package com.google.mu.protobuf.util

Class ValueConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.mu.protobuf.util.ValueConverter
  • public class ValueConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    A converter that can convert a Pojo to Value message, and recursively, the Collections, Maps and Tables thereof into corresponding ListValue or Struct wrappers.

    Users can implement custom conversion logic while delegating to the default implementation for the standard supported types.

    For example, if the application needs to convert User types to Value by using the user ids: 

    
 ValueConverter customConverter = new ValueConverter() {
   protected Value convert(Object obj) {
     if (obj instanceof User) {  // custom logic
       return super.convertToValue(((User) obj).getId());
     }
     return super.convert(obj);  // else delegate to default implementation
   }
 };
 Struct userStruct = customConverter.struct(ImmutableMap.of("user1", user1));
    Since:
    5.8

      • toStruct

        public final BiCollector<java.lang.CharSequence,​java.lang.Object,​com.google.protobuf.Struct> toStruct()
        Returns a BiCollector that accumulates the name-value pairs into a Struct with the values converted using toValue(java.lang.Object).

        Duplicate keys (according to Object.equals(Object)) are not allowed.

        Null keys are not allowed, but null values will be represented with NullValue.

        Can also be used to create Struct literals conveniently, such as: 

        
 BiStream.of("foo", 1. "bar", true).collect(converter.toStruct());

      • convertRecursively

        protected com.google.protobuf.Value convertRecursively​(java.lang.Object object)
        If object is of type Iterable, Map, Multimap or Table, apply this converter recursively and wrap the converted elements into ListValue or Struct. Otherwise delegates to convert(java.lang.Object).

        Subclasses can override this method to convert custom recursive types. Must not return null.
